Exxaro Climbs to Highest Level Since June 2008 as Annual Profit Increases

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-02-17T08:11:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/exxaro-climbs-to-highest-level-since-june-2008-as-annual-profit-increases.html
  Exxaro Resources Ltd ., a South
African coal mining company, climbed to the highest in more than
2 1/2-years after saying full-year profit surged.  The stock gained as much as 2.85 rand, or 1.8 percent, to
161.35 rand, its highest intraday level since June 3, 2008, and
was trading at 159.51 rand as of 10:08 a.m. in Johannesburg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  